description:
In this video, I breakdown a Euroleague game featuring Bayern Munich and Partizan. The primary offense for both of these teams is ballscreen continuity. The pace, spacing, and understanding of how to manipulate the defense is second to none. 

You'll learn about what "tag" defenders are. The difference between a "step up" screen and a "simple" or "get" screen. You'll see why getting two defenders to guard 1 is so important, and you'll see some of the nuances that happen in Europe that you don't always see in the USA.
